YELLOW FEVER IN ASIA (5)
========================
[1]
Date: Mon, 4 Mar 1996 19:28:03 -0800 (PST)
From: Jonathan Mayer <jmayer@u.washington.edu>
This "good" medical geographer has been curious about the question for a
long time, and I finally got a decent answer from Duane Gubler at CDC
when he was at the University of Washington last month. Part of it is
competition from dengue, as previously noted--and there were a couple of
other factors that he speculated about, but no really definitive answer.
I'd really like to put some time and effort into studying the question
more definitively--any collaborators out there?
