[3]
From: "Reiter, Paul I." <ipr1@CIDVBI2.EM.CDC.GOV>
Date: Tue, 05 Mar 96 08:59:00 EST
Quick comments
Yellow fever does not abound in South America. It is endemic, but only in
its sylvatic habitat where it circulates between forest monkeys, with
occasional monkey to human transmission. The last urban outbreak was many
years ago (Trinidad in 1954 I think). The next outbreak is harder to
predict! Dengue is of course very prevalent in most tropical cities, and
is ubiquitous in South America.
Dengue viruses travel happily between the continents in humans, in jet
planes. For example, the dengue 3 strain that recently arrived in Central
America and is spreading rapidly throughout the region is a Sri Lanka/South
Indian strain. Thus we cannot think in terms of geographically isolated
dengue populations.
The minimum infection rate in wild mosquito populations, even during
epidemics, would reduce the probability of interaction between viruses in
the same mosquito to very low levels, too low to make exclusion of one by
the other a possibility. If there is any mutual exclusion between dengue
and yellow fever it would only be feasible by virtue of the immune system
of the host. However, it is worth mention that both diseases were rampant
in the Americas in the last century.
Paul Reiter
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[- The outbreak in Trinidad was in the early 1980s. YF in Trinidad has always
been of interest because of its close proximity to Venezuela and whether the
virus could maintain itself on the island or whether it depended on "fresh"
deliveries of airborne mosquitoes or whatever. Quoting from memory, the
"1980" outbreak was classical in starting in unvaccinated forest workers.
Affected monkeys were collected and unfortunately held in the Port-of-Spain
zoo. When the PH risk was belatedly appreciated, they were sacrificed.
Basically the more the authorities looked, the more virus they found in the
resident forest monkey population but it was in an "incomplete" form. Because
each virus isolation from yet another monkey resulted in a formal note to WHO
and affected the cruise and tourist trade, the national programme was
terminated. MH-J
